 treatment_protocol_ch1 :

All patients included in this study were pathologically diagnosed with HBV-infected hepatocellular carcinoma and received lenvatinib (12 mg/day for bodyweight ≥ 60 kg or 8 mg/day for bodyweight < 60 kg) orally once daily and a PD-1 inhibitor intravenously on day 1 of a 21-day treatment cycle. The anti-PD-1 antibodies and their single-dose infusion were sintilimab 200 mg, pembrolizumab 200 mg, tislelizumab 200 mg, or toripalimab 240 mg. 
